cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a framework that embeds high level rules into deep reinforcement learning to accelerate the learning process and make the system more stable. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a framework that combines rule-based knowledge with deep learning. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as deep reinforcement learning is commonly used in robotics and control systems. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as the proposed framework could potentially be applied to multi-agent systems where high level rules can be used to coordinate the actions of multiple agents.
